01:04:42.382 --> 01:04:43.883
Dear David Bowie,

01:04:44.050 --> 01:04:48.513
sometimes it seems like things
actually work out.

01:04:53.351 --> 01:04:58.982
English, Irene. English. There is
no such thing as conversational Elvish.

01:05:00.358 --> 01:05:03.028
Sorry, Dewey.

01:05:05.363 --> 01:05:07.574
It's what they call you, isn't it?

01:05:07.741 --> 01:05:08.950
No.

01:05:09.117 --> 01:05:12.120
It was at your last school.
Or do you prefer "Junior"?

01:05:12.287 --> 01:05:14.748
Do you know your buddy,
his full name is Will Burton, Jr.?

01:05:14.914 --> 01:05:16.291
Did you know that I don't care?

01:05:16.458 --> 01:05:18.126
Well, he told you
his dad was famous, right?

01:05:18.293 --> 01:05:21.087
Or infamous, right, Dewey?
I mean, you still close to the old man?

01:05:21.254 --> 01:05:22.881
You probably don't get to talk to him
much anymore, do you?

01:05:23.048 --> 01:05:26.801
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Well, I think you do, Dewey.

01:05:26.968 --> 01:05:30.055
I think you do, Dewey.

01:05:36.519 --> 01:05:40.315
Okay, that was surreal. Are you okay?

01:05:40.482 --> 01:05:43.985
I don't... I got... I gotta...

01:05:53.828 --> 01:05:55.872
What are you doing?

01:05:56.039 --> 01:05:59.459
You didn't answer my texts,
and you left me alone with the monsters.

01:05:59.626 --> 01:06:01.628
Sorry, I'm sick.

01:06:01.795 --> 01:06:05.715
My spidey-sense tells me you're lying.

01:06:06.383 --> 01:06:08.593
I'm thinking about changing schools.

01:06:08.760 --> 01:06:12.013
No way, my little friend. I'm not facing
the Neanderthals without you.

01:06:12.180 --> 01:06:17.519
Besides, if you change schools,
then you can't gain access to this.

01:06:18.728 --> 01:06:21.189
- What's that?
- Something private.

01:06:21.356 --> 01:06:24.901
Something I would only show
the manager of my band.

01:06:25.068 --> 01:06:27.862
Or my best friend.

01:06:28.029 --> 01:06:30.365
Scooch.

01:06:31.533 --> 01:06:34.869
Okay. You said we needed one song
that says who we are.

01:06:35.036 --> 01:06:38.289
Well, these say who I am.

01:06:40.583 --> 01:06:43.378
Little brothers.

01:06:44.004 --> 01:06:47.090
Little brothers again.

01:06:48.758 --> 01:06:50.677
- For your dad?
- No.

01:06:50.844 --> 01:06:53.263
Not for him, exactly.

01:06:53.430 --> 01:06:55.598
Inspired by him, I guess.
You know, things he said to me.

01:06:55.765 --> 01:06:59.185
But it's not just about my dad anymore.
That'd be, hello, weird.

01:06:59.352 --> 01:07:02.230
It's about everything.

01:07:02.397 --> 01:07:04.566
Wow, that's articulate.

01:07:04.733 --> 01:07:05.900
You know, there's other stuff in here, too.

01:07:06.067 --> 01:07:09.404
- I'm not saying any of it's good...
- Thanks.

01:07:09.571 --> 01:07:15.285
Hey. By accepting this, it means that there
will be no more talk of changing schools.

01:07:15.452 --> 01:07:17.787
Agreed?

01:07:19.539 --> 01:07:22.167
- Man, I'm good.
- Charlotte!

01:07:22.334 --> 01:07:24.878
- Charlotte! My mom is in the...
- I knew you were ticklish.

01:07:25.045 --> 01:07:28.590
You are so ticklish, I knew it.

01:07:29.299 --> 01:07:33.636
Somebody wanna tell me
what's going on in here?

01:07:35.555 --> 01:07:37.432
Get off his bed.

01:07:37.599 --> 01:07:40.727
Wait. You don't think...

01:07:40.894 --> 01:07:43.271
I saw you kiss him in the car.

01:07:43.438 --> 01:07:45.482
Well, that was
for educational purposes only.

01:07:45.648 --> 01:07:46.608
I wanna die.

01:07:46.775 --> 01:07:49.152
Did you hear that? He wants to die.
He needs help, Karen.

01:07:49.319 --> 01:07:51.363
Then I'll help him. I'm his mom.

01:07:51.529 --> 01:07:53.531
But I am wise in the ways of Will.

01:07:53.698 --> 01:07:58.161
I'm actually here, you know. These covers
don't literally make me disappear.

01:07:58.328 --> 01:08:00.747
You know what I think?
I think you're full of it, Charlotte.

01:08:00.914 --> 01:08:03.249
And when I think someone's full of it,
I don't trust them.

01:08:03.416 --> 01:08:05.335
Mom, will you stop interfering?

01:08:05.502 --> 01:08:08.296
Sorry, I'm not your friend,
I'm your mother. That's my job.

01:08:08.463 --> 01:08:12.759
No, Mom, you're supposed to give me
a little breathing room so I can have a life,

01:08:12.926 --> 01:08:15.220
instead of just saying that's what you want.

01:08:15.387 --> 01:08:18.055
- He's got a point, Karen.
- And you, I'm not a manager.

01:08:18.223 --> 01:08:23.770
I don't take on the biggest band
in school and change destiny. I can't.

01:08:23.978 --> 01:08:28.024
Will you both just please leave me alone?

01:08:31.694 --> 01:08:34.113
Get out.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:48.377
- Somebody called me Dewey today.
- What? How?

01:08:48.545 --> 01:08:51.589
- He must've found out about Dad.
- I hate them all.

01:08:51.756 --> 01:08:53.966
- Me too.
- You, however, I love.

01:08:54.134 --> 01:08:58.430
Yeah, but you married Dad.
We can't really trust your taste.

01:08:58.595 --> 01:09:02.142
I was 19. And he was a drummer.

01:09:02.434 --> 01:09:05.687
And overnight it made my mother
finally take me seriously,

01:09:05.854 --> 01:09:07.229
which is really all I wanted.

01:09:07.397 --> 01:09:08.356
- Mom?
- I... What?

01:09:08.523 --> 01:09:11.568
You're doing that thing
where you talk to me like I'm Oprah.

01:09:11.734 --> 01:09:17.115
I'll tell you this, though.
I'd marry him all over again to get you.

01:09:21.411 --> 01:09:25.415
I promise you're going to get
everything you deserve out of life.

01:09:25.582 --> 01:09:29.336
And a little bit of the next guy's.

01:09:38.928 --> 01:09:41.598
I'll never be

01:09:41.848 --> 01:09:45.769
A knight in armor with a sword in hand

01:09:47.187 --> 01:09:50.189
Ora kamikaze fighter

01:09:51.358 --> 01:09:54.109
Don't count on me

01:09:54.277 --> 01:09:58.281
To storm the barricades and take a stand

01:10:00.325 --> 01:10:03.161
Or hold my ground

01:10:04.329 --> 01:10:08.124
You'll never see any scars or wounds

01:10:09.334 --> 01:10:12.087
I don't walk on coals

01:10:12.253 --> 01:10:15.298
I won't walk on water

01:10:16.341 --> 01:10:19.052
I am no prince

01:10:19.302 --> 01:10:21.971
I am no saint

01:10:22.222 --> 01:10:25.767
I am not anyone's wildest dream

01:10:27.894 --> 01:10:31.064
But I will stand behind

01:10:31.940 --> 01:10:35.443
And be someone to fall back on

01:10:44.786 --> 01:10:47.580
That's the song.

01:10:56.840 --> 01:10:59.134
Some comedy

01:10:59.300 --> 01:11:01.052
You're bruised and beaten down

01:11:01.219 --> 01:11:05.306
And I am the one who's looking for a favor

01:11:06.474 --> 01:11:08.768
Still, honestly

01:11:08.935 --> 01:11:12.564
You don't believe me
But the things I have

01:11:12.731 --> 01:11:15.900
Are the things you need

01:11:16.317 --> 01:11:20.113
You look at me like I don't make sense

01:11:20.280 --> 01:11:24.576
Like a waste of time
Like it serves no purpose

01:11:25.785 --> 01:11:29.205
I am no prince
I am no saint

01:11:30.665 --> 01:11:34.627
And if that's what you believe you need

01:11:35.545 --> 01:11:38.882
You're wrong
You don't need much

01:11:39.049 --> 01:11:42.635
You need someone to fall back on

01:11:45.055 --> 01:11:48.850
And I'll be that
I'll take your side

01:11:49.768 --> 01:11:52.729
If I'm the only one

01:11:53.229 --> 01:11:56.024
I'm used to that

01:11:57.067 --> 01:11:59.277
I've been alone

01:11:59.444 --> 01:12:02.113
I'd rather be

01:12:04.199 --> 01:12:06.701
The half of us

01:12:06.868 --> 01:12:08.995
The least of you

01:12:09.162 --> 01:12:11.873
The best of me

01:12:13.958 --> 01:12:16.211
And I will be

01:12:16.378 --> 01:12:20.298
I'll be your prince
I'll be your saint

01:12:21.132 --> 01:12:25.428
I will go crashing through fences
in your name

01:12:27.138 --> 01:12:29.349
I will, I swear

01:12:29.516 --> 01:12:33.061
I'll be someone to fall back on

01:12:34.062 --> 01:12:37.315
I'll be the one who waits

01:12:37.899 --> 01:12:41.361
And for as long as you let me

01:12:41.820 --> 01:12:45.115
I will be the one you need

01:12:46.491 --> 01:12:50.036
I'll be someone to fall back on

01:13:03.842 --> 01:13:07.012
Someone to fall back on

01:13:14.769 --> 01:13:17.731
One to fall back on

01:13:28.950 --> 01:13:31.786
Dear David Bowie,

01:13:32.912 --> 01:13:36.958
just when it looked like things
might be okay,

01:13:37.125 --> 01:13:38.335
disaster struck.

01:13:38.501 --> 01:13:41.087
What's going on? Where is everybody?

01:13:41.254 --> 01:13:45.884
- Art class is cancelled today.
- Why? What happened?

01:13:46.634 --> 01:13:50.180
Charlotte's father passed away.

01:13:51.181 --> 01:13:53.975
I assumed you knew.

01:13:54.142 --> 01:13:56.311
No.

01:14:09.199 --> 01:14:12.702
This was a mistake. We shouldn't be here.

01:14:12.869 --> 01:14:16.581
She didn't return any of my calls.

01:14:18.291 --> 01:14:20.418
- You going to be okay?
- Yeah.

01:14:20.585 --> 01:14:22.837
Okay.

01:14:23.338 --> 01:14:27.175
Go, she's your friend. She needs you.

01:14:35.767 --> 01:14:38.812
Boys...
- I got them.

01:14:48.738 --> 01:14:51.241
Charlotte?

01:14:53.243 --> 01:14:55.745
I'm sorry.

01:14:58.998 --> 01:15:00.333
I called.

01:15:00.500 --> 01:15:04.671
I don't know if you got any of my messages.

01:15:05.630 --> 01:15:08.883
Yeah, I got them. Thanks.

01:15:10.176 --> 01:15:13.138
I wish you would've called me back.

01:15:13.304 --> 01:15:14.639
Why?

01:15:14.806 --> 01:15:16.141
"Why?"

01:15:16.307 --> 01:15:18.893
I don't know. I mean, you told Ben.

01:15:19.060 --> 01:15:21.229
So?

01:15:21.813 --> 01:15:22.814
Is anything wrong?

01:15:22.981 --> 01:15:24.357
Yeah.

01:15:24.524 --> 01:15:25.650
Yeah, my dad died.

01:15:25.817 --> 01:15:27.277
No, I know.

01:15:27.444 --> 01:15:32.198
I wish I could've met him.
I'm sure he was a great man.

01:15:33.491 --> 01:15:35.827
He was.

01:15:37.287 --> 01:15:40.123
I got to do this.

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:44.502
Charlotte.

01:15:48.048 --> 01:15:49.674
- What do you want, Will?
- What do I want?

01:15:49.841 --> 01:15:51.593
I just want you to know that I'm here
for you.

01:15:51.760 --> 01:15:53.428
Okay, got it. What else?

01:15:53.595 --> 01:15:56.473
And not to worry about the daycare.
I can handle that until you come back.

01:15:56.639 --> 01:15:57.599
That's it.

01:15:57.766 --> 01:15:58.641
Listen, I'm sorry, okay.

01:15:58.808 --> 01:16:01.144
It's just a lot to deal with right now,
and I sort of want to be alone.

01:16:01.311 --> 01:16:02.437
Okay. I get it, yeah.

01:16:02.604 --> 01:16:03.646
And look, about the band...

01:16:03.813 --> 01:16:08.443
Don't even worry about the band, okay?
We'll use Phil's Song for Bandslam.

01:16:08.610 --> 01:16:11.237
Or not. We don't have to use Phil's Song.
We can find another song, or...

01:16:11.404 --> 01:16:15.200
Hey, go ahead. Knock yourselves out.

01:16:18.495 --> 01:16:21.706
I mean, it's a beautiful song, Charlotte.

01:16:21.873 --> 01:16:24.167
It would make your dad proud.
It would be like he's there.

01:16:24.334 --> 01:16:27.212
Stop! Please, just stop!

01:16:27.379 --> 01:16:29.172
There is no us, Will. I'm not in the band.

01:16:29.339 --> 01:16:32.592
What? No, no, no.
Okay, we'll find another song...

01:16:32.759 --> 01:16:35.553
It's not about the song. I quit. I just quit.

01:16:35.720 --> 01:16:37.013
- Why?
- I don't do "why"!

01:16:37.180 --> 01:16:40.892
No, you have to. You just have to!

01:16:47.273 --> 01:16:49.609
Please.

01:16:55.699 --> 01:16:58.034
You really want to know why?

01:16:58.201 --> 01:17:01.913
Last summer, when my dad got sick,

01:17:02.914 --> 01:17:06.376
I promised God, the universe,

01:17:08.294 --> 01:17:10.755
anyone who'd listen,

01:17:10.922 --> 01:17:13.049
that I'd be different.

01:17:13.216 --> 01:17:15.927
Better. Nicer.

01:17:17.846 --> 01:17:21.433
My dad hated the way I acted
when I was with Ben.

01:17:21.599 --> 01:17:24.811
The way I treated kids who weren't popular.

01:17:24.978 --> 01:17:27.564
So, I changed.

01:17:27.731 --> 01:17:32.944
I started volunteering with the monsters.
I left my friends. I left my band.

01:17:33.111 --> 01:17:37.657
I left everything that set me apart
from people like...

01:17:37.824 --> 01:17:39.993
Me.

01:17:42.829 --> 01:17:45.582
People like me.

01:17:47.500 --> 01:17:50.295
So we were just this

01:17:50.462 --> 01:17:53.256
experiment to try and make your dad okay?

01:17:53.423 --> 01:17:55.216
No, I know how crazy this must sound...

01:17:55.383 --> 01:17:58.303
Honestly, Charlotte,
the thing that never made sense

01:17:58.470 --> 01:18:02.640
was you being my friend in the first place.

01:18:04.642 --> 01:18:07.896
Hey!
While you're up there on your high horse,

01:18:08.063 --> 01:18:11.399
ask yourself who are you
to judge me about lying?

01:18:11.566 --> 01:18:13.860
Dewey!

01:18:19.699 --> 01:18:21.951
That stands for DWI, right?

01:18:22.118 --> 01:18:25.413
Driving while intoxicated?

01:18:26.373 --> 01:18:29.668
I don't know what's worse.

01:18:30.710 --> 01:18:36.091
Losing a father you love so much
you change your whole life for him,

01:18:39.427 --> 01:18:45.141
or having a father you're so ashamed of,
you make up a whole life for him.

01:19:20.176 --> 01:19:22.846
Can I have some beef jerky?

01:19:23.013 --> 01:19:25.724
Is he kidding?

01:19:27.976 --> 01:19:31.021
You warned me about her.

01:19:31.187 --> 01:19:32.814
I didn't listen.

01:19:32.981 --> 01:19:37.861
She can't help it.
It's how girls like that are hardwired.

01:19:39.320 --> 01:19:42.365
How are we hardwired?

01:19:42.657 --> 01:19:46.703
I mean, sure, right now, I am just a kid.

01:19:47.746 --> 01:19:50.206
Whatever.

01:19:51.875 --> 01:19:54.711
What's going to change?

01:19:54.878 --> 01:19:57.005
Nothing.

01:19:57.172 --> 01:19:59.716
I'm just going to be

01:19:59.883 --> 01:20:02.302
unhappy,

01:20:04.012 --> 01:20:05.722
alone,

01:20:05.889 --> 01:20:09.309
scared of, like, everything.

01:20:12.979 --> 01:20:16.149
You're not alone, Will.

01:20:23.740 --> 01:20:27.577
Experiment? We were just her experiment?

01:20:27.744 --> 01:20:29.537
I keep thinking...

01:20:29.704 --> 01:20:30.914
What?

01:20:31.081 --> 01:20:35.251
Well, if you were just part of
Charlotte's experiment this whole time,

01:20:35.418 --> 01:20:37.796
then, what is reality?

01:20:37.962 --> 01:20:39.881
What if Charlotte and her experiment are

01:20:40.048 --> 01:20:43.426
really a part of someone else's
larger experiment?

01:20:43.593 --> 01:20:48.264
I mean, what if we're being manipulated
by some greater intelligence than our own?

01:20:48.431 --> 01:20:53.061
And if so, is there really such a thing
as free will?

01:20:54.104 --> 01:20:55.355
Am I moving my hand,

01:20:55.522 --> 01:20:59.609
or was it predetermined by a force
I'm not even aware of?

01:20:59.776 --> 01:21:03.113
Charlotte times a trillion.

01:21:11.579 --> 01:21:14.040
See, this is why you don't have friends!

01:21:14.207 --> 01:21:17.502
All right, this is ridiculous! She doesn't
get to make our whole lives a lie!

01:21:17.669 --> 01:21:22.215
I mean, it was real for me.
Wasn't it real for you?

01:21:22.799 --> 01:21:25.135
I say we refuse to let Charlotte
screw this up for us.

01:21:25.301 --> 01:21:28.805
I mean, we've worked too hard.

01:21:29.472 --> 01:21:31.599
We're doing Bandslam.

01:21:31.766 --> 01:21:32.809
You're crazy.
Why?

01:21:32.976 --> 01:21:35.353
How long have you got?

01:21:35.520 --> 01:21:38.273
It won't work.
What song are we going to do?

01:21:38.440 --> 01:21:39.858
Phil's Song. She said we could.

01:21:40.025 --> 01:21:43.862
Oh, yeah? And who's going to sing it?

01:22:29.407 --> 01:22:33.620
You say your patience is longer
than my face

01:22:35.246 --> 01:22:40.001
Oh, yeah, but I can see right through
your plastic case

01:22:40.794 --> 01:22:45.799
Oh, you're running round
like your life is some type of race

01:22:46.800 --> 01:22:51.137
You know I'm trying
but I cannot keep your pace

01:22:51.596 --> 01:22:54.766
Oh, so take your blizzard
somewhere else, little girl

01:22:54.933 --> 01:22:58.186
Your stormy weather ain't welcome here

01:22:58.353 --> 01:23:00.897
I Can't Go On, I'll Go On.

01:23:01.064 --> 01:23:04.317
Can't not buy it, buy it.

01:23:07.612 --> 01:23:10.281
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:23:11.241 --> 01:23:13.952
How are the guys holding up?
Have you been backstage?

01:23:14.119 --> 01:23:17.163
Yeah, they're fine. Actually, they're great.

01:23:17.330 --> 01:23:20.542
Think I'll go and wish them luck.

01:23:20.709 --> 01:23:22.961
Okay.

01:23:29.968 --> 01:23:32.971
Hey! Dennis Ardmore.

01:23:33.179 --> 01:23:34.055
What?

01:23:34.222 --> 01:23:37.475
Dennis Ardmore.
Does that name ring a bell?

01:23:37.642 --> 01:23:39.394
No. Should it?

01:23:39.561 --> 01:23:43.940
I guess not. I just didn't know how much
research you all had done, so...

01:23:44.107 --> 01:23:46.484
But he would've been about your age now.

01:23:46.651 --> 01:23:49.696
Except that Will's father got drunk in
the middle of the afternoon,

01:23:49.863 --> 01:23:51.406
like he did every afternoon,

01:23:51.573 --> 01:23:56.327
and ran him over while he was walking
home from school.

01:23:56.703 --> 01:23:57.620
I heard. I'm sorry.

01:23:57.787 --> 01:24:01.833
Yeah. Did you hear that Will insisted
that I bring him to the funeral?

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:03.918
That's what kind of kid he is.

01:24:04.085 --> 01:24:08.298
Twelve years old, he walks right up to
Dennis Ardmore's parents,

01:24:08.465 --> 01:24:11.885
and asked their forgiveness.

01:24:17.849 --> 01:24:19.768
Everyone hated Will's dad.

01:24:19.934 --> 01:24:22.187
Well, who wouldn't? I mean...

01:24:22.354 --> 01:24:26.941
And then they put him away, and it's
like they just turned it all on his kid.

01:24:27.108 --> 01:24:29.778
It was awful.

01:24:29.986 --> 01:24:31.237
So just give him a break.

01:24:31.404 --> 01:24:34.783
Please? Not a lot of people have.

01:24:34.949 --> 01:24:40.538
So I don't know what you were planning
on saying to him, or doing, but just don't.

01:24:40.705 --> 01:24:42.082
Just don't. Okay?

01:24:42.248 --> 01:24:46.461
Don't make up with him. Don't be his friend.

01:24:46.920 --> 01:24:47.879
Why not?

01:24:48.046 --> 01:24:53.051
Because, I don't think he'll recover
if you leave him twice.

01:24:55.345 --> 01:24:57.847
I've never met a kid like Will.

01:24:58.014 --> 01:24:59.933
My friends have never met a kid like Will.

01:25:00.100 --> 01:25:03.228
The monsters have never met a kid like Will.

01:25:03.395 --> 01:25:07.190
And I want you to let me apologize to him
because I want to keep knowing him.

01:25:07.357 --> 01:25:09.943
You know, I like who I am
when I'm with Will.

01:25:10.110 --> 01:25:15.115
And I will do anything in the world
to be that person again.

01:25:17.325 --> 01:25:19.869
So, please,

01:25:21.830 --> 01:25:24.833
don't ask me not to.

01:25:30.463 --> 01:25:32.507
Okay.

01:25:32.674 --> 01:25:35.176
Thank you.

01:25:35.719 --> 01:25:37.220
I said, "Okay. " I'm not going to hug you.

01:25:37.387 --> 01:25:39.055
Okay.

01:25:39.222 --> 01:25:41.516
And by the way,
I'm really glad you don't wear

01:25:41.683 --> 01:25:43.977
those little groupie outfits
all the time, Karen.

01:25:44.144 --> 01:25:46.980
You'll need this.

01:25:50.108 --> 01:25:51.985
All right.

01:25:52.152 --> 01:25:55.905
And I'm so sorry about your father.

01:26:14.215 --> 01:26:17.385
Tax and total it for me

01:26:21.389 --> 01:26:24.976
I'll pay my bill and run so fast

01:26:30.440 --> 01:26:33.735
Separation is our love now

01:26:35.737 --> 01:26:38.239
Well, we're toast.

01:26:38.406 --> 01:26:41.618
I don't know. They're okay.

01:26:41.785 --> 01:26:42.911
I hear the band to watch

01:26:43.078 --> 01:26:48.333
is I Can't Drive Stick, I'll Drive Stick,
or something like that.

01:26:52.587 --> 01:26:55.757
Look, let me just speak.

01:26:55.924 --> 01:27:00.261
The whole experiment thing,
not my finest hour.

01:27:01.221 --> 01:27:05.767
I was angry and stupid
and really, really confused.

01:27:07.602 --> 01:27:10.313
And I'm sorry.

01:27:13.483 --> 01:27:15.110
Are you kidding me?

01:27:15.276 --> 01:27:16.820
Okay, quick recap.

01:27:16.986 --> 01:27:19.781
Charlotte dumps Ben,
turns you guys into a band,

01:27:19.948 --> 01:27:22.117
finds the genius that is Will,

01:27:22.283 --> 01:27:25.620
then, does one stupid thing

01:27:25.829 --> 01:27:27.789
because her father has died,

01:27:27.956 --> 01:27:31.626
realizes, and comes to apologize.

01:27:32.293 --> 01:27:36.464
And you're not going to
accept the apology?

01:27:36.965 --> 01:27:40.427
Plus, I really miss you guys.

01:27:42.804 --> 01:27:45.223
Is that real?

01:27:45.390 --> 01:27:47.684
Hundred percent.

01:27:47.851 --> 01:27:53.732
The only thing that matters is seeing
you guys kick some serious butt tonight.

01:27:54.149 --> 01:27:57.068
And you're singing Phil's Song.

01:27:57.235 --> 01:28:00.947
- Is that okay?
- Yeah. Of course.

01:28:01.406 --> 01:28:06.703
And I'll be the girl in front,
screaming my head off while you do.

01:28:18.965 --> 01:28:21.092
Keep it hot like steam, that's your dream

01:28:21.259 --> 01:28:23.011
Baby, get up off me

01:28:23.178 --> 01:28:26.514
It's so clean, the way I've been
Gots me looking glossy

01:28:26.681 --> 01:28:29.893
On the scene with the queen
That be acting bossy

01:28:30.060 --> 01:28:34.147
I don't want no drama, little mama
So please get up off me

01:28:34.314 --> 01:28:37.525
Yeah, you know how I blow
Till you're feeling dizzy

01:28:37.692 --> 01:28:41.154
Lots of soul, that's the goal

01:28:41.780 --> 01:28:44.115
Yeah, go ahead. Copy that.

01:28:44.282 --> 01:28:46.159
Way to be impartial.

01:28:46.326 --> 01:28:49.371
Way to be realistic about your chances.

01:28:49.537 --> 01:28:51.664
Way to say "way" just because I did.

01:28:51.831 --> 01:28:55.085
Yeah. Standing by. Follow spots.

01:28:55.251 --> 01:28:59.881
And now, from Martin Van Buren
High School in Lodi, New Jersey,

01:29:00.048 --> 01:29:03.593
Ben Wheatly and the Glory Dogs!

01:29:06.638 --> 01:29:09.557
You're number one!

01:29:13.353 --> 01:29:15.855
Thank you.

01:29:18.650 --> 01:29:21.569
Thank you so much.

01:29:22.070 --> 01:29:27.367
I'd like to dedicate this next song
to someone very special to me.

01:29:28.451 --> 01:29:30.203
She taught me a lot,

01:29:30.370 --> 01:29:32.914
and she wrote this song.

01:29:33.081 --> 01:29:36.793
So, Charlotte, this one's for you.

01:29:40.755 --> 01:29:42.966
I'll never be

01:29:43.133 --> 01:29:47.053
A knight in armor with a sword in hand

01:29:47.303 --> 01:29:50.390
Whoa, whoa! No, no, no!

01:29:50.557 --> 01:29:52.600
Don't count on me

01:29:52.767 --> 01:29:56.354
To storm the barricades and take a stand

01:29:56.521 --> 01:29:58.773
I didn't know. I swear. I didn't know.

01:29:58.940 --> 01:30:00.275
- No, no, no.
- What?

01:30:00.442 --> 01:30:02.527
You'll never see

01:30:02.694 --> 01:30:06.448
It's old. Ben knew it. He probably thought
he was doing something nice for me.

01:30:06.614 --> 01:30:09.325
I had no idea, Karen.
You've got to believe me!

01:30:09.492 --> 01:30:11.244
I am no prince

01:30:11.411 --> 01:30:12.996
I am no saint

01:30:13.163 --> 01:30:16.166
I am not anyone's wildest dream

01:30:16.332 --> 01:30:18.835
What are we going to do?
We can't sing the same song.

01:30:19.002 --> 01:30:21.880
I don't know anything else.

01:30:22.047 --> 01:30:23.048
Yes, you do.

01:30:23.214 --> 01:30:26.426
And it's famous and only has, like,
four chords.

01:30:26.593 --> 01:30:27.927
Alley. Now!

01:30:28.094 --> 01:30:31.264
Someone to fall back on

01:30:50.784 --> 01:30:53.953
Someone to fall back on

01:31:13.431 --> 01:31:14.683
Come on!

01:31:14.849 --> 01:31:15.892
We need another minute.

01:31:16.059 --> 01:31:17.143
We don't have another minute! They just...

01:31:17.310 --> 01:31:20.480
We need another minute!

01:31:25.777 --> 01:31:29.489
Our last band is also from
Martin Van Buren High.

01:31:29.656 --> 01:31:31.950
I don't know what they're putting
in the water in Lodi,

01:31:32.117 --> 01:31:36.371
but give it up for I Can't Go On, I'll Go On!

01:31:40.291 --> 01:31:43.211
That's us! Come on!

01:31:43.378 --> 01:31:44.629
What's going on?

